                    <comment id="13236545" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 12:45:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also fixed end() offset bug in the ngram tokenizers...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13236548" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 12:50:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, we know the ngramtokenizers truncate to the first 1024 chars, but that &lt;br/&gt;
doesn&apos;t mean they can&apos;t implement end() correctly so that at least&lt;br/&gt;
highlighting on multivalued fields etc works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13236549" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 12:53:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;oh one thing: i think we should blast the filter versions of these the same way?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;e.g. if i have mocktokenizer + (edge)ngramfilter, are they ok?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13236806" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 17:26:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The ngram filters are unfortunately not OK: they use up tons of RAM when you send random/big tokens through them, because they don&apos;t have the same 1024 character limit... I think we should open a new issue for them... in fact I think repairing them could make a good GSoC!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13236816" author="rcmuir" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 17:30:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see... well +1 for this commit, its an improvement!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13236820" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 23 Mar 2012 17:33:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK I opened &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3907&quot; title=&quot;Improve the Edge/NGramTokenizer/Filters&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3907&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for ngram love...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
